</li><li> <a class='twikilink' href='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForgingScene' title='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForgingScene'>Forging Scene</a>  <br />A scene dedicated to forging a kickass weapon or something.
</li><li> <a class='twikilink' href='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FriendToAllChildren' title='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FriendToAllChildren'>Friend to All Children</a>  <br />A gentle character is fond of children.
</li><li> <a class='twikilink' href='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FutileHandReach' title='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FutileHandReach'>Futile Hand Reach</a>  <br />When something bad happens to a character, the protagonist will reach out towards the character in question.
</li></ul></div>
<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder6');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;G&nbsp;</div><div id="folder6" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<ul ><li> <a class='twikilink' href='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GalleySlave' title='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GalleySlave'>Galley Slave</a>  <br />The hero is enslaved and forced to work as a galley rower.
</li><li> <a class='twikilink' href='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenericCopBadges' title='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenericCopBadges'>Generic Cop Badges</a>  <br />Badges and car decals in many cop shows are generic, with just the word "Police."
</li><li> <a class='twikilink' href='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenocideDilemma' title='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenocideDilemma'>Genocide Dilemma</a>  <br />Where an entire planet of people is out to destroy Earth - do we get them first?
