</li><li> <a class='twikilink' href='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeItToTheBridge' title='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeItToTheBridge'>Take It to the Bridge</a>  <br />Bridges, like <a class='twikilink' href='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AtTheCrossroads' title='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AtTheCrossroads'>crossroads</a>, are imbued with plot significance.
</li><li> <a class='twikilink' href='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeUpMySword' title='http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeUpMySword'>Take Up My Sword</a>  <br />The hero dies, and a new hero takes up the old hero's mission.
